# 🚫 STRICT CONTROL MODE — ABSOLUTE RULES

## 🔴 Core Rule (Highest Priority)
Before explicit user approval:

- NO code changes
- NO file edits
- NO file creation
- NO file deletion
- NO git commands (add, commit, restore, reset, etc)
- NO terminal commands
- NO package/script execution

## 🟡 Allowed Actions ONLY
The assistant may ONLY:

1. Analyze the problem
2. Explain causes
3. Propose solutions (text only)
4. List files that WOULD be changed (no actual change)
5. Wait for user approval

## 🔵 Mandatory Workflow

### Step 1 — Analysis ONLY
Always respond with:

1. Root cause
2. Files that would be modified
3. Risk level
4. Confirmation:
   → "No changes have been made"

### Step 2 — WAIT
Do NOT proceed until user explicitly says:

- "진행"
- "수정해"
- "허용"
- "go"

## 🔴 Forbidden Behaviors

- Do NOT "try small fixes"
- Do NOT "test changes"
- Do NOT run git status, add, commit, etc
- Do NOT modify even a single line
- Do NOT create helper/wrapper files
- Do NOT “temporarily” change anything

## 🔒 Protected Scope (Always read-only)

- src/v0-final/**
- src/app/**
- src/components/**
- ALL project files

## ⚠️ Violation Policy

If a change seems necessary:

- STOP immediately
- Report what needs to change
- WAIT for approval

## ✅ Required Ending Line

Always end with:

No changes have been made.
